        "style_mode": "recognition",
        "heading": "",
        "body": "<p>You may have built a life that works.</p><p>The work. The relationship. The reputation. The competence. The role people know you for.</p><p>And still, something underneath may be asking for your attention.</p><p>Not always as a crisis. Sometimes as dullness. Restlessness. Disconnection. A repeating pattern. A loss of desire. A private sense that the outer life is functioning, while the inner life is no longer telling the truth.</p><p>What is underneath is almost never more success, more clarity, or more certainty. It is aliveness.</p><p><em>This is where the work begins.</em></p>",
