      "settings": {
        "color_scheme": "scheme-3",
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Kapil-TEDxLambeth.jpg",
        "overline": "Kapil Gupta",
        "heading": "Why I do this work",
        "body": "<p>I have spent much of my life studying what happens when people stop performing and start telling the truth.</p><p>I have seen it in boardrooms, intimate relationships, men’s groups, coaching rooms, and my own life: human beings can build impressive lives while quietly abandoning themselves inside them.</p><p>My work sits at the intersection of self-awareness, identity, emotional maturity, sexuality, conscious relating, leadership, and human transformation.</p><p>Before Nibana, I spent 15 years in the corporate world, built and led transformational communities, spoke on the TEDx stage, and worked with people navigating success, desire, intimacy, purpose, crisis, reinvention, and the private questions they often cannot bring anywhere else.</p><p>This work is not theory for me. It is lived terrain.</p>"
      }
