        "overline": "The Method",
        "heading": "From Performance to Presence",
        "body": "<p>Most people do not lose themselves all at once.</p><p>They adapt. They achieve. They become useful. They become impressive. They become who life, family, work, success, or survival required them to become.</p><p>Performance is not the enemy. It is the self you have learned to manage, protect, and present. For a long time, it works. It is often how we survive, build, lead, love, and belong.</p><p>But at some point, the performed life starts to cost too much.</p><p>The Performance to Presence Method is a way of seeing what has been running beneath the surface, meeting it honestly, and learning to live from a deeper centre.</p>",
        "bridge": "This journey is supported by four areas of work: Identity Work, Inner Skills, Philosophy & Play, and Practices.",
